This paper is about Dialog State Tracking (DST) in task-oriented dialog systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper proposes a new approach for DST that combines the advantages of picklist-based and span-based methods, which involves machine learning techniques such as classification and feature extraction, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper presents empirical results on a dataset, which involves experimental design and statistical analysis, so cs.SD (Sound) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories.
